

Running hackaroo locally:

  sudo apt-get install ruby
  sudo gem install webrick
  cd hackaroo
  server-start


Exercises

  To add an exercise, create a new file in 'exercises' directory and update 
  hackaroo/exercise-data.js.
  
  Good sources for inspiration:
  
  http://mislav.uniqpath.com/poignant-guide/
  http://hackety-hack.com/
    https://github.com/hacketyhack/hacketyhack/tree/master/lessons
  http://learncodethehardway.org/
  http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11246/best-resources-to-learn-javascript
  https://developer.mozilla.org/en/A_re-introduction_to_JavaScript
  http://eloquentjavascript.net/
  http://ejohn.org/apps/learn

Development Notes
=====================================

libraries used:

  for rendering the result:
    prototype
    jcanvascript

  for the editor
    prototype
    codemirror2
    showdown

